title: Return type notation ICEs on return position impl trait in trait

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

body:
Reproducer from [`impl_trait_utils`](https://github.com/google/impl_trait_utils): ```rust #![feature(return_position_impl_trait_in_trait, return_type_notation)] trait IntFactory { fn stream(&self) -> impl Iterator; } trait SendIntFactory: IntFactory + Send {} ``` Which results in: ``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/hir/map/mod.rs:845:18: expected item, found HirId(DefId(0:4 ~ trait_transformer_test[f0a7]::IntFactory::stream).0) (trait method `stream` in IntFactory::stream) ``` This works with async functions just fine. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.71.0-nightly (9d871b061 2023-05-21) binary: rustc commit-hash: 9d871b0617a4b3d6610b7cee0ab5310dcb542c62 commit-date: 2023-05-21 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.71.0-nightly LLVM version: 16.0.4 ```
